[{"body": "PT Bank Amar Indonesia Tbk (AMAR) has partnered with Julo Group, a leading fintech lending platform, to offer embedded banking services to Julo's 2.58 million users, providing comprehensive banking features and loan solutions within one application, with credit facilities of up to IDR 50 million. This strategic collaboration is expected to strengthen Julo's position as a trusted financial partner for underserved users, addressing a critical gap in financial services for millions of Indonesians.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52052/amar-bank-embedded-banking-julo", "sub_sector": ["banks"], "tags": ["Fintech", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["AMAR.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T17:02:52", "title": "Amar Bank partners with Julo Group to offer embedded banking services and loan solutions to 2.58 million users."}, {"body": "The Financial Services Authority (OJK) is encouraging financial institutions to provide housing ownership loans to low-income households, offering flexibility in lending policies based on risk management practices. This initiative aims to support President Prabowo Subianto's housing program, which targets 3 million homes per year, and has already seen 2.35 million new credit accounts granted to debtors with previous non-performing loans as of November 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52051/ojk-urges-financial-institutions-ease-mortgage-loans-low-income-families", "sub_sector": ["financing-service"], "tags": ["Financial Ratios", "Debt", "Interest Rates", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T16:51:59", "title": "Indonesian Financial Services Authority Encourages Lenders to Offer Housing Loans to Low-Income Households"}, {"body": "DBS Bank Ltd (DBS) divested 23.20 million shares of PT Sarimelati Kencana Tbk (PZZA), reducing its stake from 5.56% to 4.8% of PZZA's total issued and paid-up capital of 3.02 billion shares, with an estimated transaction value of IDR 4.73 billion. The transaction resulted in DBS Bank Ltd's shareholding decreasing to 144.93 million shares from 168.14 million shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52050/dbs-bank-divests-shares-pzza", "sub_sector": ["consumer-services"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Executive Changes", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["PZZA.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T15:27:19", "title": "DBS Bank Ltd sells 23.2 million shares of PT Sarimelati Kencana, reducing its stake in the Indonesian Pizza Hut franchise operator."}, {"body": "PT Medco Energi Internasional Tbk (MEDC) signed a loan agreement with its subsidiary Medco Bell Pte. Ltd. for USD 435.3 million, which will be used for tendering, refinancing, and/or repaying debt, and will not impact MEDC's financial condition as it is not separately reflected in consolidated financial statements. As of September 2024, MEDC's total assets stood at USD 7.68 billion, with cash and cash equivalents of USD 606.45 million.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52049/medco-extends-idr-loan-subsidiary", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Debt", "Energy Commodities", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["MEDC.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T15:20:24", "title": "Medco Energi's subsidiary signs USD 435.3 million loan agreement with no interest."}, {"body": "PT Cisarua Mountain Dairy Tbk (CMRY) has utilized IDR 1.37 trillion of its IDR 3.57 trillion initial public offering (IPO) proceeds, with IDR 903.44 billion allocated for production capacity expansion, IDR 223 billion for distribution channel expansion, and IDR 251.06 billion for working capital and other activities. The company still has IDR 2.19 trillion in remaining IPO funds, with a majority placed in time deposits, demand deposits, and bonds, and is targeting IDR 8.97 trillion in revenue for 2024, a 15.47% increase from last year's IDR 7.7 trillion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52048/remaining-ipo-proceeds-cmry-parked-deposits-bonds", "sub_sector": ["food-beverage"], "tags": ["IPO", "IDX", "Earnings Report", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["CMRY.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T14:22:18", "title": "Cimory Utilizes 38.58% of IPO Proceeds for Capacity Expansion and Working Capital."}, {"body": "PT Adiwisata Finansial Teknologi, through its fintech lending platform Danai.id, has partnered with PT Bank JTrust Indonesia Tbk (JTRO) to promote blue economy development in Indonesia, offering inventory financing facilities to micro, small, and medium enterprises in the fishery and sea-related product industry. Since its establishment in 2018, Danai.id has channeled over IDR 760 billion in credit with a 99.06% loan repayment success rate, and this collaboration is expected to have a significant positive impact on MSME development in the ocean economy sector.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52042/danaiid-trust-bank-synergise-blue-economy", "sub_sector": ["banks"], "tags": ["Fintech", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Economic Reports", "Sharia Economy", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BCIC.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T10:46:21", "title": "PT Adiwisata Finansial Teknologi partners with PT Bank JTrust Indonesia to promote blue economy development in Indonesia through financing access for micro, small, and medium enterprises."}, {"body": "The Jakarta Composite Index (JCI) strengthened in the morning session, reaching 7,032.3 at 9:56 am WIB, a slight increase from 7,017.76 at 9 am WIB, with stocks like PT Alamtri Resources Indonesia Tbk, PT Bukit Asam Tbk, and PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk showing positive gains. However, large market capitalization issuers such as PT Bayan Resources Tbk, PT Bank Central Asia Tbk, PT Barito Renewables Energy Tbk, and PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk suppressed the JCI's climb.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52041/morning-session-jci-climbs", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal", "banks", "oil-gas-coal", "banks", "utilities", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["ADRO.JK", "PTBA.JK", "BBRI.JK", "BYAN.JK", "BBCA.JK", "BREN.JK", "TLKM.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T10:24:56", "title": "Jakarta Composite Index Rises Slightly in Morning Session but Fails to Reach Yesterday's High"}, {"body": "PT Aneka Tambang Tbk (ANTM) has partnered with Java Integrated Industrial Ports Estate (JIipe) to construct a smelting facility, leveraging JIipe's advanced infrastructure and national vital object status to reduce foreign exchange reserves and boost local product utilization. The collaboration is expected to accelerate precious metal refining and drive sustainable industry growth in Indonesia, with Antam gaining direct access to high-purity gold and benefiting from JIipe's reliable utility and transportation infrastructure.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52040/antam-jiipe-planning-smelter-gresik", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["Metals and Minerals", "Gold", "IDX", "Market Trends", "JII70", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["ANTM.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T10:14:05", "title": "ANTAM Partners with Java Integrated Industrial Ports Estate to Develop Smelting Facility and Boost National Economy."}, {"body": "PT Petrosea TBK (PTRO) has denied any plans for collaboration with PT Raharja Energi Cepu TBK, a newly debuted company owned by Happy Hapsoro, despite rumors of a potential partnership. PTRO, which has a strong track record as a contractor, having secured a IDR 4.6 trillion contract from BP Berau Ltd last year, is capable of supporting PT Raharja Energi Cepu TBK's plans to increase participation rights in the Cepu bloc and explore new investment opportunities in the Kasuri bloc, West Papua.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52039/ptro-joins-hands-happy-hapsoros-ratu", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Energy Commodities", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["RATU.JK", "PTRO.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T09:57:18", "title": "Petrosea TBK Denies Plans for Collaboration with Ratu Cepu Amid Rumors of Potential Partnership."}, {"body": "Herwin Hidayat, Director of PT Bumi Resources Minerals Tbk (BRMS), acquired 2.32 million shares of BRMS with a total transaction value of IDR 997.68 million, or IDR 430 per share, in a personal investment through direct ownership. The acquisition took place last Friday, with BRMS' share price closing 4.67% lower at IDR 408 per share on Monday, after peaking at IDR 438 and dipping to IDR 406 per share.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 2, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52037/bumi-resources-minerals-boss-bag-brmss-shares", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["Executive Changes", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BRMS.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T07:54:30", "title": "Bumi Resources Minerals Director Herwin Hidayat Acquires 2.32 Million Shares Worth IDR 997.68 Million."}, {"body": "The Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index (JCI) fell 1.02% or 71.99 points to 7,016.88 on Monday, with PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI), PT Barito Renewables Energy Tbk (BREN), and PT Astra International Tbk (ASII) being the top drags on the index. However, big caps such as PT Chandra Asri Pacific Tbk, PT Dian Swastatika Sentosa Tbk, and PT Merdeka Copper Gold Tbk helped to mitigate the decline, with the energy, basic materials, and healthcare sectors being the only ones to show positive performance.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52036/dropping-bbri-bren-shares-drove-jci", "sub_sector": ["banks", "utilities", "multi-sector-holdings", "basic-materials", "oil-gas-coal", "basic-materials"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Market Sentiment", "Neutral"], "tickers": ["BBRI.JK", "BREN.JK", "ASII.JK", "TPIA.JK", "DSSA.JK", "MDKA.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-14T06:06:05", "title": "Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index Falls 1.02% to 7,016.88 on Monday Trading."}, {"body": "Foreign investors sold a net 2.99 billion shares on Monday, with PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO) experiencing the highest net sell of 194.12 million shares, followed by PT Bumi Resources Minerals Tbk (BUMI) and PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI). On the other hand, PT Kawasan Industri Jababeka Tbk (KIJA) saw the largest net buy of 52.61 million shares, followed by PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur Tbk (BIPI) and PT Barito Pacific Tbk (BRPT).", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52035/foreign-trades-decline-sell-share", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services", "basic-materials", "banks", "properties-real-estate", "oil-gas-coal", "basic-materials"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "IDX Composite", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BRMS.JK", "BBRI.JK", "KIJA.JK", "BIPI.JK", "BRPT.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-13T19:31:18", "title": "Foreign investors sell 2.99 billion shares in Indonesian stock market, with PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia TBK experiencing the highest net sell."}, {"body": "PT Kawasan Industri Jababeka Tbk (KIJA) led the net foreign buy leaderboard with 52.61 million shares, closing at IDR 196 per share with a total transaction value of IDR 39.83 billion. PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur Tbk (BIPI) followed as the runner-up with 50.84 million shares, closing at IDR 84 per share with a total transaction value of IDR 9.28 billion.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "properties-real-estate", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52034/kija-leads-week", "sub_sector": ["properties-real-estate", "oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["IDX", "Foreign Investor", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["KIJA.JK", "BIPI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-13T17:58:04", "title": "Jakarta-based PT Kawasan Industri Jababeka Tbk leads in net foreign buys with 52.61 million shares on Monday's trading session."}, {"body": "PT Brigit Biofarmaka Teknologi TBK (OBAT) aims to increase sales by 20% this year, following a strong performance in 2024 with total sales exceeding IDR 100 billion and net profit reaching IDR 30 billion, representing a 30% net profit margin. The company attributes its success to its self-sustaining spirulina cultivation and plans to adopt digital marketing strategies to position itself as a one-stop maklon service provider, aiming to surpass its 20% growth target.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52033/obat-targets-growth-eyeing-nutritious-meal-program", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal", "retailing", "apparel-luxury-goods", "heavy-constructions-civil-engineering", "properties-real-estate", "heavy-constructions-civil-engineering", "oil-gas-coal", "automobiles-components", "food-beverage", "basic-materials", "banks", "banks", "oil-gas-coal", "food-beverage", "consumer-services", "oil-gas-coal", "logistics-deliveries", "oil-gas-coal", "properties-real-estate", "banks", "industrial-goods", "basic-materials", "food-beverage", "investment-service", "food-staples-retailing", "food-beverage", "food-beverage", "industrial-goods", "properties-real-estate", "basic-materials", "software-it-services", "industrial-goods", "utilities", "properties-real-estate", "banks", "food-beverage", "retailing", "heavy-constructions-civil-engineering", "insurance", "properties-real-estate", "properties-real-estate", "software-it-services", "oil-gas-coal", "basic-materials", "software-it-services", "technology-hardware-equipment", "food-beverage", "basic-materials", "banks", "retailing", "banks", "consumer-services", "telecommunication", "banks", "properties-real-esta