ials.com/news/52027/aiming-tons-production-dgwg-targets-fertilizer-plant", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["IPO", "Fertilizers", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-13T13:46:45", "title": "PT Delta Dunia Wacana to Expand Fertilizer Plant Capacity in Palembang After Successful IPO."}, {"body": "PT Indika Energy Tbk (INDY) has appointed MacMahon Holding Limited (MAH) to develop the Awak Mas gold mining project in South Sulawesi, with a mining services contract valued at USD 463 million over a seven-year term, with an option to extend for another five years. The project, which has potential resources of 2.29 million ounces and potential reserves of 1.45 million ounces, is currently in the development phase and is expected to commence in the middle of this year.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52026/indy-assigns-macmahon-awak-mas-project", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Metals and Minerals", "Gold", "IDX", "Energy Commodities", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["INDY.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-13T12:03:00", "title": "Indika Energy appoints Macmahon to develop Awak Mas gold mining project in South Sulawesi with a seven-year contract valued at USD 463 million."}, {"body": "PT Delta Dunia Makmur Tbk (DGWG) has officially listed on the Indonesia Stock Exchange, raising IDR 202.94 billion from its initial public offering (IPO) of 882.35 million shares at IDR 230 per share, with 53.2% of the funds allocated for working capital and 46.8% for its subsidiary. The company is targeting double-digit growth this year, with a 25% net profit increase and 15-20% revenue growth, and its shares have already risen 21.74% to IDR 280 per share.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52025/debuting-dgwg-targets-double-digit-growth", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["IPO", "IDX", "IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "Earnings Report", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["DOID.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-13T11:50:10", "title": "PT Delta Giri Wacana TBK Lists on Indonesia Stock Exchange, Raises IDR 202.94 Billion in IPO"}, {"body": "PT Solusi Sinergi Digital Tbk (SURGE) has seen a 155% increase in its stock price from IDR 149 to IDR 380 per share since early 2024, with a peak of IDR 458 on November 14, 2024. Following a series of acquisitions, top-tier entrepreneurs, including Hashim S. Djojohadikusumo, Arwin Rasyid, and Fadel Muhammad, now hold significant indirect ownership stakes in SURGE, with Hashim owning 22.55% and Arwin and Fadel each owning 7.50% of the company's shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52024/national-figures-interest-wifi-shares-surge", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Mergers & Acquisitions", "Executive Changes", "IDX Composite", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["WIFI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-13T10:44:00", "title": "Surge's promising business prospects in technology infrastructure attract top-tier entrepreneurs, leading to significant changes in share ownership."}]